    <reapack name="REAPER Audio Tag.lua" type="script" desc="REAPER Audio Tag">
      <metadata>
        <description><![CDATA[{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 \fmodern Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\f1 REAPER Audio Tag} is a macOS-only REAPER action for local clip-level audio tagging.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 ReaPack installs the Lua UI and the project's shipped Python source only. You install Python 3.11, the Python dependencies, and {\f1 Cnn14_mAP=0.431.pth} yourself.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Run {\f1 REAPER Audio Tag: Configure} to validate the Python and model paths before analysis.\par}
}
]]></description>
